---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const page = {
  title: "Professional Lawn Mowing | Edwards Landscape Group",
  description: "Keep your yard picture-perfect with Edwards Landscape Group's weekly mowing program in Lynchburg and Central Virginia. Precise cuts, clean edges, and reliable schedules.",
  keywords: "lawn mowing lynchburg, weekly mowing service, lawn maintenance VA, grass cutting"
};
---

<BaseLayout {...page}>
<main>
      <section class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen" style="background-image: url('images/Mowing_service.jpg');">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-6 hero-content-block">
              <div class="hero-kicker">Mowing</div>
              <h1 class="mb-3">Cleaner cuts and crisp edges on a reliable route</h1>
              <p class="mb-4 lead">Slim, TruGreen-style header with left-aligned copy—built for quick reads and easy calls to action.</p>
              <div class="hero-meta mb-4">
                <span class="tg-badge">Weekly during peak growth</span>
                <span class="tg-badge">Edging &amp; trimming included</span>
                <span class="tg-badge">Blower cleanup every stop</span>
              </div>
              <div class="hero-actions d-flex flex-wrap">
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary mr-2 mb-2">Get on the route</a>
                <a href="services.html" class="btn btn-outline-light mb-2">All services</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-info-bar">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="info-grid">
            <div class="info-item">
              <h3>Route discipline</h3>
              <p>Dedicated mow day with text updates if weather changes the cadence.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <h3>Precision finish</h3>
              <p>Alternating patterns, clean edging on beds and drives, and blower cleanup each visit.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-item">
              <h3>Healthy height</h3>
              <p>Deck settings tuned by season to protect roots, reduce weeds, and keep stripes bold.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">How we mow</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">The route-first mowing formula</h2>
          <div class="row align-items-start gutter-40">
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <div class="tg-card h-100">
                <h3>Three-part visit</h3>
                <ul class="checklist">
                  <li>Notify and stage equipment off hard surfaces to protect edges.</li>
                  <li>Cut with fresh blades, alternating directions to avoid ruts.</li>
                  <li>Trim, edge, and clear clippings from beds, patios, and drives.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
              <div class="tg-card highlight-card h-100">
                <h3>Smart timing</h3>
                <p class="mb-3">We adjust cadence the way TruGreen tunes programs—more touches when turf is surging, fewer when it needs a breather.</p>
                <ul class="pill-list">
                  <li>Weekly April–June</li>
                  <li>Bi-weekly July–August</li>
                  <li>Weekly September–October</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary mt-2">Set my schedule</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section bg-light">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Season game plan</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Stay ahead of growth cycles</h2>
          <div class="service-timeline">
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">1</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Spring ramp-up</h4>
                <p>Higher cuts promote deep roots while we edge every hard surface for a clean start.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">2</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Summer protect</h4>
                <p>Raise the deck to reduce stress, alternate patterns, and monitor drought impacts.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-step">
              <div class="timeline-dot">3</div>
              <div>
                <h4>Fall refine</h4>
                <p>Lower the height slightly for leaf fall, edge beds again, and prep for over-seeding.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Route options</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Choose the cadence that fits your lawn</h2>
          <div class="row gutter-40">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
              <table class="comparison-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th style="width: 38%">Package</th>
                    <th>What you get</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td><strong>Standard weekly</strong><br />Suburban lots, consistent stripes</td>
                    <td>
                      <div class="mini-badges">
                        <span>Weekly (April–June)</span>
                        <span>Bi-weekly (summer)</span>
                        <span>Final pass in late fall</span>
                      </div>
                      <p class="mb-0">Full mow, trim, and blowdown with pattern rotation to protect turf health.</p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><strong>Estate weekly</strong><br />Large lots &amp; berms</td>
                    <td>
                      <div class="mini-badges">
                        <span>Two-crew option</span>
                        <span>Dedicated lead</span>
                        <span>Seasonal scalping prep</span>
                      </div>
                      <p class="mb-0">Extended time for berms, banks, and tree lines plus optional bed touch-ups each visit.</p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><strong>Prime &amp; polish</strong><br />For listings and events</td>
                    <td>
                      <div class="mini-badges">
                        <span>48-hour turnaround</span>
                        <span>Edge refresh</span>
                        <span>Spot reseed</span>
                      </div>
                      <p class="mb-0">One-off cleanup with crisp edging, blower detail, and light touch seeding where thin.</p>
                    </td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5">
              <div class="service-accordion">
                <details open>
                  <summary>How do you protect irrigation heads?</summary>
                  <p>We log head locations during the first visit and keep decks higher near spray zones. Trim crews sweep heads before edging.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                  <summary>Can you mow around play sets or gardens?</summary>
                  <p>Yes—smaller equipment and string trimming keeps delicate spaces safe. We can also block areas from service if you prefer.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                  <summary>Do you haul clippings?</summary>
                  <p>We mulch mow by default to feed the turf, but we can bag and remove on request for event weeks or first cuts of the season.</p>
                </details>
              </div>
              <div class="cta-strip">
                <p class="mb-0">Tell us your property size and preferred day—we'll slot you into the right route.</p>
                <a href="contact.html" class="btn btn-primary">Book my slot</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="service-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-label">Bundle-friendly</div>
          <h2 class="mb-4">Keep the lawn sharp between visits</h2>
          <div class="tg-card-grid three-col">
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Bed detailing</h3>
              <p>Fresh edges, weed pulls, and mulch touch-ups to keep borders crisp next to the stripes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Fertilization</h3>
              <p>Balanced nutrition and weed control so cuts stay lush and color holds through heat.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-card">
              <h3>Aeration + seeding</h3>
              <p>Core aeration and seed to thicken turf, making each mow look cleaner and fuller.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
